  "instructions": "<p>You can hunt here as early as level 300 but 350+ is recommended to hunt more comfortably. The damage isn't too high while running the creatures but if you get trapped or stop to box the damage can add up quickly, especially when you have many Tunnel Tyrants on you.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>‚öóÔ∏è Most rooms are quite open which does make it easy to run the creatures and you could begin your box when they are at lower health. It is definitely possible to hunt this spawn with mana potions but I preferred Great Spirit Potions while full boxing as they could combo quite high.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>üí∞ Your profit can depend on the price of suspicious devices on your server. I was typically looting 10-12 Suspicious Devices per hour and they were worth 18k on my server at the time of recording.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>üí∏ The cost to access the spawn makes it not a great area if you only have time for a quick 1 hour hunt. Though the profit will still cover the cost of entrance this becomes a better spawn when you are able to hunt for a longer duration, or return multiple times in the same 8 hour period as you'll only have to pay the entrance fee the once.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>üí° You will not be kicked of the dungeon after 8 hours. This means you can enter the spawn 7 hours and 59 minutes after you first entered the portal and still do a full hunt. You can even logout within the spawn and come back more than 8 hours later and still be able to do your hunt without having to pay for access again unless you leave the spawn.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>üêó I was killing around 360 Tunnel Tyrants and 270 Cave Devourers per hour. This is a good option if you are looking for a free spawn that will allow you to complete 2 hard category bestiaries at once. It would be best to come here if you managed to roll both creatures or wanted to roll them multiple times in a row. Or if you just wanted to complete these entries then continue hunting here for more time to cover the entrance fee.</p>",
